Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveA fourth-term PDP federal lawmaker seeking another term butted in on a stakeholder meeting in Nsukka Local Government Area of Enugu, and calamity followed on Saturday.
Hon. Pat Asadu representing Nsukka/Igbo-Eze South in the House of Representatives has spent 16 years in the House of Reps, and his people appeared to have had enough of him.
A source hinted that several other aspirants were earlier at the PDP meeting where they made their intentions known.
In the free-for-all that followed their declarations, people were seen in a trending video jumping fences as they fled.
Many have condemned the incident.
